<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="425" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1131,1480]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1131,1156]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is found in coastal inshore waters on sandy substrata; the Red Sea record is confirmed on the basis of a dozen specimens collected by trawl off Jizan, 
<collectingCountry box="[894,1047,1167,1192]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="24" pageNumber="425">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
, from a depth range of 
<quantity box="[1327,1432,1168,1192]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" unit="m" value="22.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="21.0">
21– 
<specimenCount box="[1368,1432,1168,1192]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" type="generic">24 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fowler" box="[151,490,1203,1228]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" refString="Fowler, H. W. &amp; Steinitz, H. (1956) Fishes from Cyprus, Iran, Iraq, Israel and Oman. Bulletin of the Research Council of Israel, 5 B (3 / 4), 260 - 292." type="journal article" year="1956">
Fowler &amp; Steinitz (
<number box="[367,428,1203,1228]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" value="1956.0">1956</number>
: 
<number box="[439,483,1203,1228]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" value="276.0">276</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
listed a single specimen of 
<quantity box="[803,858,1204,1228]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
SL from Eilat without a description (at present this specimen is lost, D. Golani, pers. comm.); 
<bibRefCitation author="Golani" box="[665,1010,1239,1264]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" refString="Golani, D. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V. (2010) The fishes of the Red Sea - reappraisal and updated checklist. Zootaxa, 2463, 1 - 135." type="journal article" year="2010">
Golani &amp; Bogorodsky (
<number box="[943,1002,1240,1264]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
did not include the species in their checklist, and noted that “all previous records (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Dor" box="[717,824,1276,1300]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" refString="Dor, M. (1984) Checklist of the Fishes of the Red Sea. Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem, xxi + 427 pp." type="book" year="1984">
Dor 
<number box="[767,824,1276,1300]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) are probably misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuvier, 1830" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1830" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Pomadasys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kaakan">
<emphasis box="[1221,1436,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="425">Pomadasys kaakan</emphasis>
(Cuvier, 
<number box="[252,314,1312,1336]" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" value="1830.0">1830</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
”. The largest specimen of 
<quantity box="[629,721,1312,1336]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.88" pageId="24" pageNumber="425" unit="cm" value="18.8">18.8 cm</quantity>
SL has a deeper preorbital and a broader interorbital space in comparison with smaller specimens; more specimens are required to see the dynamics of changes of these two characters with growth. The species can be distinguished easily from other Red Sea congeners 
